com.communote.server.core.property

Class ObjectPropertyAccessor<O extends Propertyable,P extends StringProperty>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.communote.server.core.property.PropertyAccessor<O,P,String>
      • com.communote.server.core.property.StringPropertyAccessor<O,P>
        • com.communote.server.core.property.ObjectPropertyAccessor<O,P>
  • Type Parameters:
    O - the object having the properties
    P - the type of property to handle
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AttachmentPropertyAccessor, ExternalObjectPropertyAccessor, NotePropertyAccessor, TopicPropertyAccessor, UserPropertyAccessor

    public abstract class ObjectPropertyAccessor<O extends Propertyable,P extends StringProperty>
extends StringPropertyAccessor<O,P>
    Object property accessor for string properties. The "object" in ObjectPropertyAccessor stands for the assignment of property directly to one object. In database you can see only one foreign key relation of property table.
    Author:
    Communote GmbH - http://www.communote.com/
